>some people come here with great writing skills
It honestly doesn't take that much to move into that tier.
Even the writers that give a story a half-hearted proofread before binning tend to be better at the basic literary skills.
The tradeoff is they are more likely to ignore autistic storytelling and established properties for their own worlds.
For every person enthusiastic about WKW or other longform pieces, there's ten that lack the talent to write a competent Krystal/Isabelle fic.
And from that, for every one of those there's ten that just read and CBF'ed to think about the shitposters.

Part of my undying hope is that someone takes inspiration from somethingaboutsharks, me, or another writer. They man up, hit the keyboard, and put their soul in the words.
Only the ones that conquer the fear of being afraid make it, and may fortune favor the foolish.
